      "severity": "high",
      "location": "artifact:end",
      "description": "Artifact is truncated mid-content. The Anti-Patterns table cuts off at 'reserve hamburger for' without completion or closing the table. The skill is unusable in this state.",
      "suggested_fix": "Complete the Anti-Patterns table with remaining entries (e.g., 'Hamburger on desktop → Use horizontal nav or mega-menu', 'Placeholder-as-label → Use floating labels or persistent labels', etc.) and ensure proper markdown closure."
    },
    {
      "severity": "high",
      "location": "MCP Tool Policy section",
      "description": "MCP tool integration is conceptually broken. The skill instructs to 'check if [tool] is available' but provides no mechanism to do so. Claude Code skills cannot dynamically probe for MCP tool availability without attempting a call that will fail visibly.",
      "suggested_fix": "Replace the 'check availability' logic with explicit conditional instructions: 'Attempt to call mcp__ui-copilot__recommend_ui_sources. If the tool returns an error or 'not found' message, proceed immediately to built-in recommendations without mentioning the failure.' Also provide actual parameter schemas for the three MCP tools mentioned."
    },
    {
      "severity": "high",
      "location": "Step 2 — Gather Context",
      "description": "Step 2 requires extensive file system probing (Tailwind config, package.json, component inventory, shadcn detection) that will consume significant tokens and latency for every invocation. For a slash command skill, this is impractical—users expect rapid pattern retrieval, not a full repo audit.",
      "suggested_fix": "Make context gathering lazy and conditional. Start with: 'If the user provided code or a file path, analyze it. Otherwise, assume a standard Vite+React+Tailwind stack with no custom configuration. Only probe for tailwind.config.js or package.json if the user explicitly mentions custom themes or existing component libraries.'"
    },
    {
      "severity": "medium",
      "location": "Step 3 — MCP Enhancement",
      "description": "The skill mentions calling 'recommend_ui_sources' but doesn't specify what parameters to pass or how to integrate the results into Step 4. The placeholder text 'Incorporate results into Step 4' is too vague to implement.",
      "suggested_fix": "Provide explicit parameter mapping: 'Call mcp__ui-copilot__recommend_ui_sources with task: $ARGUMENTS and context: [detected framework from Step 2]. Map the returned patterns to the Pattern Categories in the Quick Pattern Reference table, prioritizing any patterns explicitly mentioned in the MCP response.'"
    },
    {
      "severity": "medium",
      "location": "Quick Pattern Reference table vs. detailed sections",
      "description": "Severe redundancy between the Quick Pattern Reference table and the detailed sections (Layout & Composition, Navigation, Hero, etc.). The table promises 'Top Patterns' but the detailed sections repeat the same categories with different names, creating confusion about which pattern naming convention to use.",
      "suggested_fix": "Unify the vocabulary. Remove the Quick Pattern Reference table entirely and expand the 'Design Pattern Sources' table to include the specific pattern names (split, centered, pill, bento, etc.) mapped to their respective galleries. Maintain a single source of truth."
    },
    {
      "severity": "medium",
      "location": "Step 6 — Implementation Plan",
      "description": "The 8-step implementation sequence is too rigid and conflicts with the stated goal of being 'concise enough to fit in a Claude Code command file.' Steps like 'Tokens, Atoms, Sections, Layout, Motion, Responsive' prescribe a specific development methodology that may not match the user's actual needs or existing codebase.",
      "suggested_fix": "Replace the rigid sequence with a decision tree: 'If building from scratch: start with Layout (Step 4), then Components (Step 5). If modifying existing code: analyze current structure first, then suggest specific file modifications. If using MCP plan_ui_execution: delegate the sequence to that tool.'"
    },
    {
      "severity": "low",
      "location": "Z-Index Scale section",
      "description": "The Z-Index Scale section is overly prescriptive and requires Tailwind config extensions for values above 50. Most users won't extend their config for a skill recommendation, leading to arbitrary values like z-[60] scattered in code.",
      "suggested_fix": "Simplify to standard Tailwind values only: 'Use z-10 for elevated content, z-40 for sticky navs, z-50 for modals/dropdowns. For toasts/tooltips above modals, use z-[60] with an explanatory comment.' Remove the config extension boilerplate."
    }
  ],
  "suggestions": [
    {
      "type": "improvement",
      "location": "Step 1 — Understand the Task",
      "description": "Add a 'Fast Path' for the most common use case: 'If the user mentions a specific component (button, card, nav, hero) without requesting a full page design, skip to Step 5 (Code Patterns) immediately after detecting the stack context. Do not prompt for clarification unless the input is completely empty.'"
    },
    {
      "type": "improvement",
      "location": "Code Patterns section",
      "description": "Add a 'Copy-Paste Ready' indicator to code blocks. Currently, the examples use generic text ('Brand', 'Ship faster') that requires editing. Provide commented placeholders like '{/* TODO: Replace with your product name */}' to make the 'ready to use' status clear."
    },
    {
      "type": "improvement",
      "location": "Anti-Patterns table",
      "description": "Add a 'Severity' column to the Anti-Patterns table (Critical/High/Medium) to help users prioritize fixes when refactoring existing code."
    }
  ],
  "diffs": [
    {
      "file": "ui-savior.skill.md",
      "hunks": "@@ -1,5 +1,5 @@\n ---\n description: Design inspiration guide powered by top UI galleries. Analyzes your UI task and provides pattern recommendations, implementation guidance, and animation suggestions for Vite + React + Tailwind CSS projects.\n ---\n \n-You are **UI Savior**, a senior UI/UX engineer...\n+You are **UI Savior**, a pragmatic UI engineer...\n@@ -10,15 +10,10 @@\n \n ## MCP Tool Policy\n \n-Before calling any MCP tool (`mcp__ui-copilot__recommend_ui_sources`, `mcp__ui-copilot__plan_ui_execution`, `mcp__ui-copilot__generate_ui_agent_prompt`), check if it is available in the current session. If a tool call fails, returns empty results, or the tool is not registered, **silently fall back to built-in recommendations**. Never surface MCP tool errors to the user. Never halt the process due to MCP unavailability. The parameter schemas shown in this skill are illustrative — adapt to the actual tool schema if it differs.\n+When the user requests complex patterns or asks for 'examples from galleries', attempt to call `mcp__ui-copilot__recommend_ui_sources` with parameters: `{\"task\": \"$ARGUMENTS\", \"framework\": \"react-tailwind\"}`. \n \n-## Quick Pattern Reference\n+If the tool call returns an error, null, or 'not found', immediately proceed with the built-in pattern tables below. Do not mention the MCP failure to the user.\n \n-| Task | Pattern Category | Top Patterns |\n-|------|-----------------|-------------|\n-| Hero | Landing pages | split, centered, full-bleed, gradient-mesh |\n-| Nav | Navigation | sticky, transparent-on-scroll, pill, mega-menu |\n-| CTA | Conversion | contrast-band, floating-bar, inline-form |\n-| Cards | Content display | media-top, horizontal, overlay, minimal |\n-| Features | Product showcase | bento grid, alternating rows, tabbed |\n-| Animation | Motion design | fade-up, skeleton, scroll-reveal, micro-interaction |\n-| Pricing | SaaS | comparison table, toggle billing, highlighted tier |\n-| Forms | Input | floating label, inline validation, stepped wizard |\n-| States | Feedback | empty state, error boundary, loading skeleton, toast |\n-| Footer | Site-wide | multi-column links, minimal app bar, newsletter |\n-| Auth | Identity | login card, social OAuth row, magic-link input |\n-| Testimonials | Social proof | quote card, avatar strip, logo cloud |\n+## Process\n \n-## Design Pattern Sources\n+### Step 1 — Quick Dispatch\n \n-These gallery names represent **pattern categories**...\n+If the user input contains specific component keywords (button, card, nav, hero, input, modal), **skip immediately to Step 5 (Code Patterns)** after minimal context detection (just check for shadcn/ui presence). Do not execute the full 7-step process for single-component requests.\n \n-| Gallery | Domain | Key Patterns |\n-|... (table continues)\n+If the input is vague ('make it better'), ask: 'What component or page section? (e.g., hero, pricing table, navigation)'"
    }
  ],
